    <h1>EPPS 6354 - Assignment #1</h1>
    
    <h2>Title Management System (TMS)</h2>
    <p>Title Management System (TMS) is a program that I use at my workplace, Capital One, in the Auto Finance Department. It is a third-party company that Capital One partners with to store customers' titles and information. It is used alongside another program called Titan to store and display information related to customers' auto finance loans.</p>
    
    <h3>Functions of TMS:</h3>
    <ul>
        <li>Stores customer title information</li>
        <li>Documents actions taken on accounts</li>
        <li>Tracks title perfection status and title-related processes</li>
    </ul>
    
    <h2>Titan</h2>
    <p>Titan is another program used at Capital One alongside TMS. While both display auto finance loan information, Titan provides additional features such as accessing Non-Public Information (NPI), which includes personally identifiable financial information.</p>
    
    <h2>Monarch</h2>
    <p>Monarch is used to enhance customer experience by allowing them to track the progress of their auto loans and upload necessary documents such as Power of Attorney forms, driver's license copies, and insurance documents.</p>
    
    <h2>Google Translate - Language Translation Services</h2>
    <h3>Purpose:</h3>
    <p>Google Translate provides translation services for text, speech, images, and websites.</p>
    <h3>Functions:</h3>
    <ul>
        <li>Text translation</li>
        <li>Speech translation</li>
        <li>Image translation</li>
        <li>Website translation</li>
    </ul>
    
    <h2>DoorDash - E-commerce and Food Delivery</h2>
    <h3>Purpose:</h3>
    <p>DoorDash delivers food, groceries, and other essentials. The platform connects consumers, merchants, and delivery drivers.</p>
    <h3>Functions:</h3>
    <ul>
        <li>Consumers: Browse, order, track deliveries, and leave reviews</li>
        <li>Merchants: Manage orders, update menus, and run promotions</li>
        <li>Drivers: Accept deliveries, navigate locations, and track earnings</li>
    </ul>
    
    <h2>Yelp - E-commerce and Digital Marketing</h2>
    <h3>Purpose:</h3>
    <p>Yelp helps businesses gain visibility and allows consumers to search, review, and interact with businesses.</p>
    <h3>Functions:</h3>
    <ul>
        <li>Consumers: Search businesses, leave reviews, and upload photos</li>
        <li>Businesses: Advertise, respond to reviews, and manage profiles</li>
    </ul>
    
    <h2>Importance of Data Mining</h2>
    <p>Data mining is essential as it helps analyze trends, predict consumer behavior, and enhance decision-making across various industries such as healthcare, banking, and retail.</p>
    
    <h2>Social Media System Data Tables</h2>
    <h3>Potential Tables:</h3>
    <ul>
        <li><strong>User Name Table:</strong> Stores usernames, email addresses, biographies, and number of followers.</li>
        <li><strong>Followers Table:</strong> Displays follower relationships and can be sorted by various criteria.</li>
        <li><strong>Interactions Table:</strong> Tracks user engagement such as likes, comments, and views.</li>
    </ul>
